syndrome due to interaction between inhaled corticosteroids and itraconazole." Ann Pharmacother 38 (2004): 46-9[3] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[4] Daveluy A, Raignoux C, Miremont-Salame G, et al. "Drug interactions between inhaled corticosteroids and enzymatic inhibitors." Eur J Clin Pharmacol (2009):[5] "Product Information. Entocort (budesonide)." AstraZeneca Pharma Inc, Mississauga, ON.[6] "Product Information. Victrelis (boceprevir)." Schering-Plough Corporation, Kenilworth, NJ.[7] Skov M, Main KM, Sillesen IB, Muller J, Koch C, Lanng S "Iatrogenic adrenal insufficiency as a side-effect of combined treatment of itraconazole and budesonide." Eur Respir J 20 (2002): 127-33[8] Main KM, Skov M, Sillesen IB, et al. "Cushing''s syndrome due to pharmacological interaction in a cystic fibrosis patient." Acta Paediatr 91 (2002): 1008-11[9] Molimard M, Girodet PO, Pollet C, et al. "Inhaled corticosteroids and adrenal insufficiency: prevalence and clinical presentation." Drug Saf 31 (2008): 769-74[10] Raaska K, Niemi M, Neuvonen M, Neuvonen PJ, Kivisto KT "Plasma concentrations of inhaled budesonide and its effects on plasma cortisol are increased by the cytochrome P4503A4 inhibitor itraconazole." Clin Pharmacol Ther 72 (2002): 362-369[11] De Wachter E, Malfroot A, De Schutter I, Vanbesien J, De Schepper J "Inhaled budesonide induced Cushing''s syndrome in cystic fibrosis patients, due to drug inhibition of cytochrome P450." J Calif Dent Assoc 2 (2003): 72-5[12] "Product Information. Incivek (telaprevir)." Vertex Pharmaceuticals, Cambridge, MA.[13] Kedem E, Shahar E, Hassoun G, Pollack S "Iatrogenic Cushing''s syndrome due to coadministration of ritonavir and inhaled budesonide in an asthmatic human immunodeficiency virus infected patient." J Asthma 47 (2010): 830-1[14] Jonsson G, Astrom A, Andersson P "Budesonide is metabolized by cytochrome P450 3A (CYP3A) enzymes in human liver." Drug Metab Dispos 23 (1995): 137-42[15] Edsbacker S, An